hopobject.body: What company are you calling from? desvenlafaxine indications One of the most appealing aspects of German life is the renting culture. Traditionally, tenants have enjoyed secure and affordable accommodation and felt able to treat a rental flat as a home. It’s not quite true that all Germans rent. In fact, over half own their own homes. The big difference is that the housing market here has traditionally been slow-moving. Unlike other countries with credit-fuelled housing rollercoasters, few Germans have reason to see their property as their main investment.
